Quarterly Review Cycle:

1. Collect Usage Data: Applications, adaptations, modifications
2. Identify Patterns: Common challenges, successful adaptations
3. Propose Refinements: Based on empirical evidence
4. Test Refinements: Controlled experiments with user groups
5. Implement Changes: Version updates with documentation

Annual Methodology Assessment:

· Comprehensive review of all applications
· Statistical analysis of effectiveness
· Comparison with alternative methods
· Major version release with significant refinements

