B.5.2 Replication Package

For each historical analysis chapter (6-8), provide:

1. Data: All input data in accessible formats
2. Code: Complete analysis scripts with dependencies documented
3. Environment: Docker container or conda environment specification
4. Workflow: Makefile or workflow document reproducing all analyses
5. Results: Generated outputs (networks, metrics, visualizations)

Example replication command:

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/frontier-networks/historical-analysis.git

# Set up environment
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate frontier-analysis

# Run analysis for Chapter 6
cd maritime-analysis
python run_analysis.py --frontier portuguese --period 1500-1550
python run_analysis.py --frontier dutch --period 1650-1700
python comparative_analysis.py

# Generate all figures
python generate_figures.py
```

B.5.3 Ethical Data Use Guidelines

For Indigenous and Sensitive Data:

1. Access Tiers: Public, registered, restricted based on sensitivity
2. Use Agreements: Required for sensitive data, specifying limitations
3. Attribution Requirements: Proper citation of data sources
4. Benefit Sharing: Mechanisms for communities to benefit from research use
5. Data Sovereignty: Recognition of indigenous data sovereignty rights

Historical Data Ethics:

· Acknowledgment of data limitations and biases
· Consideration of descendant community perspectives
· Responsible interpretation avoiding harmful stereotypes
· Engagement with source communities where possible

